              <div class="card-header border-0 my-2" id="mail-network">
                  <a href="#" class="btn btn-header-link collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faq7"
                     aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq7">
                      Why does Apple Mail fail to load some images with the message: "Your network preferences prevent content from loading privately", and how do I resolve it?
                  </a>
                  <div id="faq7" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="mail-network" data-parent="#faq">
                      <hr />
                      <p>
                          In Apple's Mail app, in both iOS 15+ and macOS 12+, there is a new feature called "Mail Privacy Protection". It appears that this feature
                          conflicts with Lockdown's privacy protections, and we've reported this bug to Apple. Until there is a fix available, you can simply disable
                          this redundant feature - as Lockdown Firewall already blocks trackers, and Lockdown VPN hides your IP address. Here's how to do that:
                      </p>
                      <p>
                          To disable it on iOS/iPadOS:
                      <ol>
                          <li>
                              Open the Settings app.
                          </li>
                          <li>
                              Tap "Mail".
                          </li>
                          <li>
                              Tap "Privacy Protection".
                          </li>
                          <li>
                              Disable "Protect Mail Activity".
                          </li>
                          <li>
                              Disable "Hide IP Address".
                          </li>
                          <li>
                              You may need to force quit the Mail app for the settings to apply.
                          </li>
                      </ol>
                      To disable it on macOS:
                      <ol>
                          <li>
                              Open the Mail app.
                          </li>
                          <li>
                              On the menu, click "Mail" at the top left.
                          </li>
                          <li>
                              Click "Preferences".
                          </li>
                          <li>
                              Click the "Privacy" tab.
                          </li>
                          <li>
                              Uncheck all three options.
                          </li>
                      </ol>
                      </p>
