          <h5 class="my-3 pt-2 font-weight-bold">
              App Related Questions
          </h5>

          <div class="accordion" id="app">
              <div class="card-header border-0 my-2" id="login-with-facebook">
                  <a href="#" class="btn btn-header-link collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#app1"
                     aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="app1">
                      I'm having issues logging into an app with Facebook (Messenger, WhatsApp, Instagram, etc.). How do I fix this?
                  </a>
                  <div id="app1" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="login-with-facebook" data-parent="#app">
                      <hr />
                      <p>
                          Facebook tries very hard to ensure that you are in their tracking system whether you are using Facebook, Facebook Messenger,
                          Instagram, WhatsApp or any other apps they own - as well as other apps that use their login or ad networks. Lockdown
                          blocks these tracking attempts. Here's how to fix issues that you might see with Facebook's apps, or any other
                          apps that use Facebook login or other features:
                          <br />
                      <ol>
                          <li>
                              Open Lockdown, and under Firewall, tap on "Block List".
                          </li>
                          <li>
                              Try setting both "Facebook & WhatsApp" and "Facebook Trackers" to "not blocked" in the Block List. Be sure
                              to tap "SAVE" at the top right, and let the Firewall re-activate before trying again.
                          </li>
                          <li>
                              Try to log into the app with Facebook. Once you're logged into the app, you should be able to set 'Facebook Trackers'
                              to "blocked" again. You might need to keep "Facebook & WhatsApp" set to "not blocked", depending upon the app.
                          </li>
                      </ol>
                      </p>
                  </div>
              </div>

              <div class="card-header border-0 my-2" id="whitelist">
                  <a href="#" class="btn btn-header-link collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#app2"
                     aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="app2">
                      I'm having trouble with a specific app or website. How do I whitelist it so it bypasses Lockdown?
                  </a>
                  <div id="app2" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="whitelist" data-parent="#app">
                      <hr />
                      <p>
                          Here's how to whitelist an app or website:
                      <ol>
                          <li>
                              Open Lockdown
                          </li>
                          <li>
                              Tap "Whitelist"
                          </li>
                          <li>
                              On iOS, tap the "domain-to-whitelist.com" field. Or if you're on macOS, under "Custom Domains",
                              click the "New Domain" field.
                          </li>
                          <li>
                              Enter the domain associated with the app or website you'd like to whitelist. For example,
                              "yahoo.com" (without quotation marks) will whitelist the Yahoo website.
                          </li>
                          <li>
                              On iOS, tap "Done", then "Save". On macOS, click "Add".
                          </li>
                          <li>
                              Wait for the Firewall to re-activate (it will appear to turn off and back on again). If this doesn't happen, try it
                              again and ensure that you hit "Done" and "Save" (or "Add" on Mac).
                          </li>
                          <li>
                              The site or app you added now bypasses Lockdown Privacy's Firewall and Secure Tunnel. If you are uncertain what
                              domain is associated with the app you're using, feel free to contact us at
                              <a href="mailto:team@lockdownprivacy.com">team@lockdownprivacy.com</a> and we will help you out!
                          </li>
                      </ol>
                      </p>
                  </div>
              </div>

              <div class="card-header border-0 my-2" id="facebook-block">
                  <a href="#" class="btn btn-header-link collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#app3"
                     aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="app3">
                      Why do I see Facebook being blocked, even though I don't have Facebook installed?
                  </a>
                  <div id="app3" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="facebook-block" data-parent="#app">
                      <hr />
                      <p>
                          Facebook's trackers are embedded in many (if not most) popular AppStore apps. This gives Facebook
                          information about who you are, and what you do in apps - so that Facebook can serve you advertisements
                          and other targeted content. So even if you don't have Facebook itself installed, their trackers still come
                          bundled with many popular apps. Lockdown blocks these tracking attempts.
                      </p>
                  </div>
              </div>
